This paper discusses ontology-based data access (OBDA), which is a topic related to databases and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces an extension of DL-Lite, which is a logical formalism used in ontology engineering and description logics, making cs.LO a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses rules for modifying queries, which is a topic related to software engineering and cybersecurity, making cs.SE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of domain knowledge, which is a topic related to cybernetics and systems, making cs.CY a possible sub-category.
